    <!-- ---------------------------------------------------------- -->
    <!--  ABSTRACT                                                   -->
    <!-- ---------------------------------------------------------- -->
    <abstract>
      <para>
        This repository contains empirical data and statistical analysis code
        associated with the manuscript "Capturing the unseen: a novel, low-cost
        method for stratified subterranean sampling of soil invertebrates in
        drylands." The study introduces and evaluates two subterranean pitfall-trap
        designs — a double-stratified design (two soil layers) and a
        three-stratified design (three soil layers) — deployed across ten sites in
        the Kalahari dryland system. The dataset records taxonomic identifications
        (Class, Order, Family, Subfamily, Tribe, Genus, Species), counts, and
        dry biomass of invertebrates captured between October 2024 and March 2025.
        The R code replicates all analyses reported in the manuscript, including
        generalised linear mixed models (GLMMs) of species richness and biomass,
        and Bayesian multivariate Poisson models of abundance for the dominant
        families Scarabaeidae and Tenebrionidae.
      </para>
    </abstract>

